<body>
    <h1>Quattro Formaggi Pizza</h1>
    <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Pizza dough</li>
        <li>Mozzarella cheese</li>
        <li>Gorgonzola cheese</li>
        <li>Parmesan cheese</li>
        <li>Fontina cheese</li>
        <li>Olive oil</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Instructions:</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Preheat your oven to its highest setting.</li>
        <li>Roll out the pizza dough into a circle on a floured surface.</li>
        <li>Place the dough on a pizza stone or baking sheet.</li>
        <li>Sprinkle a generous amount of mozzarella cheese evenly over the dough.</li>
        <li>Crumble gorgonzola cheese and distribute it over the mozzarella.</li>
        <li>Grate parmesan cheese and sprinkle it over the pizza.</li>
        <li>Add small pieces of fontina cheese evenly.</li>
        <li>Drizzle a bit of olive oil over the pizza.</li>
        <li>Bake in the preheated oven for about 10-12 minutes, or until the crust is golden and the cheese is melted and bubbly.</li>
    </ol>
</body>
